FAILURE 7 (mobile only): "reference/shortcuts page renders KbdHint chips"
  - Locator getByText('R').first() resolved to <h3> heading "Refresh..."
    which is hidden in mobile viewport.
  - Root cause: page snapshot shows the KbdHint chips DO render correctly
    (visible in the page-snapshot YAML — `cell -> generic "R"`), but the
    Playwright text matcher picks up the first occurrence of "R" which is
    inside the <h3> heading text "Refresh..." NOT the chip itself.
  - Locator is ambiguous: getByText('R').first() returns the heading
    'Refresh...' (since heading text starts with R).
  - Fix would be: getByRole('cell').getByText(/^R$/) for an exact match
    on the chip's cell content.
  - The DESKTOP version passes because viewport differences mean the heading
    layout interacts differently with toBeVisible.
  - Evidence dir: test-results/help-walking-checklist-Rev-baa8b--page-renders-KbdHint-chips-chromium-mobile/

