=== Console warning observed (HIGH VOLUME) ===

Throughout the run, the vite/TanStack-Router dev console emitted hundreds of:
  [vite] (client) [console.warn] Generated path "/help" for route "/_helpLayout/help"
   did not match the same route after params.stringify.

This is a console.WARN (not error), so the spec's `if (msg.type() === 'error')`
filter does NOT capture it (zero console.error expectation still holds for that
assertion — assuming anchor test gets past the article.prose check).

However, this warning indicates a route-generation mismatch in buildHelpRoutes:
the wildcard `/help/$` parameter path probably doesn't round-trip through
params.stringify. Worth investigating in a follow-up but does NOT block the
ROADMAP S2 "zero console.error" invariant (since it's console.warn).

